World richest cricket board is BCCI, with a net worth of around Rs. 18,760 crore.
The Indian Premier League (IPL) is an Indian professional Twenty20 (T20) cricket league established in 2008.
Lalit Modi is the founder of the Indian Premier League (IPL).
The Indian Premier League's (IPL) business value in 2024 is $16.4 billion, which is a 6.5% increase from the previous year.
